</p>
<p>There's at least two great things about this. First, code outside of this
class doesn't need to know <em>how</em> to figure out whether or not there was a winner:
that code can be dumb and just call this method. Second, if something happens
in the future and the logic used to figure out if there is a winner changes,
we only need to update the code in this <em>one</em> spot: no need to run around
the code base trying to figure out where we have the old logic for seeing
if there was a winner.</p>
<p>Update <code>battle.php</code> to use this. The first <code>if</code> statement is <em>really</em> trying
to figure out whether or not there was a winner. Update this to
<code>$battleResult-&gt;isThereAWinner()</code>. Use that again right below:</p>
